# Corner to Corner

A criterium simulation. The pace never lets up — surges out of every corner, attacks from the field, and a sprint finish to take the win. Stay alert, stay in position, and save something for the line.

- 5:00 50%
  - :30 Warm up — the race starts soon
  - 2:00 Easy spinning, stay loose, shake out the nerves
  - 1:30 Race starts in 1 minute
  - :30 30 seconds — clip in and get ready
- 2:00 70%..90%
  - :05 Neutral roll-out — pace is building
  - 1:00 Almost at race speed
- 10x
  - :20 130%
    - :03 SURGE out of the corner!
  - 1:00 75%
  - :15 120%
    - :03 Close the gap!
  - :45 70%
- 3:00 80%
  - :10 Settle into the pack
  - 1:00 The break went — do we chase?
  - 1:00 Bridge across!
- 6x
  - :15 140%
    - :02 ATTACK!
  - :45 75%
  - :20 130%
    - :02 Counter-attack!
  - 1:00 70%
- 3:00 80%
  - :10 Back together — bell lap coming
  - 1:30 Last lap — position is everything
  - :30 Lead-out is winding up
- :30 90%
  - :05 Get on the wheel
- :15 110%
  - :03 Wind it up...
- :15 170%
  - :02 SPRINT! Everything for the line!
- 5:00 40%
  - :10 Arms up! Great race
  - 2:00 Spin it out, cool down easy
